[{"location":"#SimpleAlgebra","page":"Home","title":"SimpleAlgebra","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for SimpleAlgebra.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"#SimpleAlgebra.Arithmetic.ScalarOp","page":"Home","title":"SimpleAlgebra.Arithmetic.ScalarOp","text":"ScalarOp(x::T, y::T) where T<:Real\n\nRepresenta una operación escalar sobre dos valores del mismo tipo. Los valores son promovidos automáticamente si los tipos no coinciden.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#SimpleAlgebra.Arithmetic.ScalarOp-Tuple{Real, Real}","page":"Home","title":"SimpleAlgebra.Arithmetic.ScalarOp","text":"ScalarOp(x::Real, y::Real)\n\nConstructor personalizado que promueve los valores a un tipo común. Esto permite escribir ScalarOp(3.5, 2) sin errores de tipo.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SimpleAlgebra.Arithmetic.ScalarOp-Tuple{Real}","page":"Home","title":"SimpleAlgebra.Arithmetic.ScalarOp","text":"ScalarOp(x::Real)\n\nConstructor adicional para ScalarOp que asume y = 0. Útil para representar un escalar como operación unaria.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#Base.:==-Tuple{ScalarOp, ScalarOp}","page":"Home","title":"Base.:==","text":"==(a::ScalarOp, b::ScalarOp) -> Bool\n\nCompara dos ScalarOp por igualdad exacta componente a componente.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#Base.isapprox-Tuple{ScalarOp, ScalarOp}","page":"Home","title":"Base.isapprox","text":"isapprox(a::ScalarOp, b::ScalarOp; kwargs...) -> Bool\n\nCompara dos ScalarOp usando Base.isapprox en cada componente. Permite tolerancias configurables.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SimpleAlgebra.Arithmetic.add-Tuple{ScalarOp, ScalarOp}","page":"Home","title":"SimpleAlgebra.Arithmetic.add","text":"add(a::ScalarOp, b::ScalarOp)\n\nSuma dos objetos ScalarOp componente a componente. Promueve los tipos si es necesario.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SimpleAlgebra.Arithmetic.div_safe-Tuple{ScalarOp, ScalarOp}","page":"Home","title":"SimpleAlgebra.Arithmetic.div_safe","text":"div_safe(a::ScalarOp, b::ScalarOp)\n\nRealiza una división segura componente a componente. Lanza un error si alguno de los divisores es cero.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SimpleAlgebra.Arithmetic.mul-Tuple{ScalarOp, ScalarOp}","page":"Home","title":"SimpleAlgebra.Arithmetic.mul","text":"mul(a::ScalarOp, b::ScalarOp)\n\nMultiplica componente a componente dos ScalarOp.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SimpleAlgebra.Arithmetic.sub-Tuple{ScalarOp, ScalarOp}","page":"Home","title":"SimpleAlgebra.Arithmetic.sub","text":"sub(a::ScalarOp, b::ScalarOp)\n\nResta componente a componente entre dos ScalarOp.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"}]
